verses.roman:
raghunātha āsi' tabe jyeṭhāre milāila
mleccha-sahita vaśa kaila--saba śānta haila

synonyms: raghunātha—Raghunātha dāsa; āsi'-coming; tabe—then; jyeṭhāre milāila—arranged a meeting between the caudhurī and the elder brother of his father; mleccha-sahita—with the Mohammedan; vaśa kaila—he settled; saba—everything; śānta haila—became peaceful.
translation: Raghunātha dāsa arranged a meeting between his uncle and the caudhurī. He settled the matter, and everything was peaceful.
